<div xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
    <head>Symbol (non meaning-bearing)</head>
    <div>
        <head>TEI</head>
        <p><specList>
                <specDesc key="g"/>
            </specList>
            <listRef>
                <ptr target="a"/>
            </listRef></p>
        <p>&lt;g&gt; (character or glyph) represents a non-standard character or glyph.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <head>EpiDoc</head>
        <p>Where a symbol is non meaning-bearing, it should be represented using the element
            &lt;g&gt;, with the following attribute: </p>
        <list type="bulleted">
            <item>@type indicates the name of the decorative symbol, e.g. leaf.</item>
        </list>
        <p>A Unicode value can be used inside the &lt;g&gt; if desired.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <cit>
            <quote>/ <!-- or Unicode for this? --></quote>
            <bibl corresp="#pn"> </bibl>
        </cit>


        <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#pn">
            <g type="slanting-stroke"/>
        </egXML>
    </div>
    <div>
        <cit>
            <quote>dr.</quote>
            <bibl corresp="#seg"/>
        </cit>

        <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#seg">
            <g type="scroll"/>
        </egXML>
    </div>
</div>
